New minus old participant proportions

2025-07-21

DIFFERENCE BETWEEN OLD AND NEW EXPERIMENT

Participant selection proportions only.

Plots of differences in proportions of participants selecting each answer, for the new experiment data minus the old experiment data.

A positive bar means the proportion was higher in the new experiment.

A prevailing pattern is participants are less sure. They have become more spread out in their answers. This is shown by many panels having a single downward pointing bar, and many small equal upward pointing bars, meaning a strong single answer has become dispersed among many others.

For example, in d101, they used to overwhelmingly select Au=1, but now that bar is much reduced (ie has a strong downward-point bar).
